<title>USA: USDA hikes assessments on pork imports next month.</title>
<headline>USDA hikes assessments on pork imports next month.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1997-05-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Agriculture Department said Tuesday it would raise assessments on imported pork and pork products beginning June 12 to reflect higher hog prices paid at major U.S. markets.</p>
<p>The increase is eight-hundredths of a cent per lb, or nineteen-hundredths of a cent per km, according to the agency's Agricultural Marketing Service.</p>
<p>Assessments on imported pork products are established by formula each year, based on U.S. market prices for hogs. The agency said the June increase in assessments reflected a 25-percent increase in hog prices paid at major U.S. markets.</p>
<p>((Washington commodities desk, 202 898 8467))</p>
